# Git: remotes (Big Daves News vs Family OS)

This repo lists **two** GitHub remotes, but they are **different projects**:

- **`origin`** — `https://github.com/dking2451/Big-Daves-News-.git` — **primary** for **Big Daves News** (iOS app + this tree).
- **`familyos`** — `https://github.com/dking2451/family-os-mvp.git` — **Family OS**; do **not** assume every change here belongs there.

## Default when the user asks to commit and push

1. Push the current branch to **`origin`** only.
2. **Do not** push to **`familyos`** unless the user **explicitly** asks to sync or push to Family OS.

If a push fails, report the error clearly.

## When the user explicitly wants both remotes

Only then push to both (replace `main` with the current branch if different):

```bash
git push origin HEAD
git push familyos HEAD
```

Optional helper from the repo root: `./scripts/push-remotes.sh` (use when intentionally updating **both** remotes).

## Shared backend / cross-repo confusion

Some **backend** or shared files may conceptually overlap with Family OS or other repos. That does **not** mean every Big Daves News commit should go to **`familyos`**. Treat **`origin`** as the source of truth for this app unless the user says otherwise.
